cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about Natural Language Processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on Clinical Named Entity Recognition (CNER). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes the use of deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of dictionaries, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with the identification and classification of clinical terms, which is related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
